genresAdvancedInfo.name: musique concrete
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This experimental music genre emerged in the mid-20th century and involves the manipulation and manipulation of recorded sounds, such as natural and industrial noises. The sounds are often cut up, reassembled and layered to create complex and abstract compositions. Musique Concrete has been used in film scores, sound installations and avant-garde performances.
